main event: Radar operators at Lisburne AFS detected two UFOs on 3/6/64 at approximately 0330 hours.
interesting points: The objects were tracked on radar for about 20 seconds before disappearing.,The UFOs were moving at a speed of approximately 70-80 knots.,No visual observation of the UFOs was made by the operators.,The radar showed a westerly course for the detected objects.,There was no physical evidence or photographs documented in the report.
